{"/service/ndnp/in/batch_in_janeway_ver01/data/sn87055779/00383349898/1930121801/0246.xml":{"full_text":"%r-:\nAuvnouni. ve<vsi\u00bbiui\nWest Side Community News\nSADIE E. BECZKIEW1CZ, Correspondent\n1148 Western Avenue Telephone 3-8288\nk\n\nStanley Mezykowski was elected\n-president of the Young Men\u2019s Glee\n\u2022club of St. Hedwige\u2019s parish at the\nyearly meeting Tuesday night. Mr.\nMezykowski succeeds Stanley A.\nCBeczkiewicz. Other officers chosen\nfollow: Theodore Dobski, vice presi\ndent; Stanley Laskowski, recording\nand financial Secretary; Thaddeus\nNiespodziany, treasurer; the Rev.\nCasimlr Wltucki, C. S. C., chaplain;\n-Prof. Casimlr P. Luzny, musical di\nrector. The new officers will be in\nstalled Jan. 18. Monthly meeting will\nbe held every third Monday of the\nvmonth. Following the business ses\nsion a smoker was enjoyed by the\nmembers. Tonight following the\n^church devotions the Glee club will\nhold a rehearsal under the direction\nof Prof. Lunzy.\nThe state commission of combined\n\u2666groups of the Polish Women Alliance\nfor Indiana will hold a yearly meet\n,ing Sunday, Jan. 4, in Michigan City.\nMrs. Antoinette Hon, president of the\n\u2022(Commission, and Miss Irene Karpin\nski, recording secretary, will attend\n.this session together with delegates\nfrom the local groups.\nAn important monthly meeting of\nthe M. R. Polish Falcons will take\nplace Sunday afternoon in Koeciuszko\nhall.\nOn New Year\u2019s day at 5 o\u2019clock In\nthe afternoon the M. R. Polish Fal\ncons together with M. R. Lady Fal\ncons will entertain with a Christmas\nparty for children. The guests will\nbe presented with gifts by a Santa\nClaus. Following the party a Joint\nsocial gathering will be held for mem\nbers of both nests.\nSOCIAL EVENTS.\nPreparations are progressing for\nthe observance of the fifth anniver\nsary of the Young People\u2019s Progress\nclub of St. Casimir\u2019s parish which\nwill be held in form of a semi-formal\ndinner-dance Monday night, Jan. 12,\nin St. Casimir\u2019s auditorium. Pro\nfessor Clarence Manion, of Notre\nDame university, and C. W. Nielsen,\ndirector of the Outing and Recreation\nBureau of Chicago, will appear on\nthe program as the principal speak\ners. The installation of new officers\nof the club will take place during the\nevening.\nMiss Clarice Kruk, 426 N. Wilbur\nstreet, was hostess to members of the\nSmile club Tuesday night at her\nhome. Bunco wras enjoyed at which\nfavors were won by Mrs. Alex Manus\nzak, Mrs. Henry Sergent and Miss\nKruk.\nThe dance committee o' St. Hed\nwlge\u2019s Athletic committee cancelled\nthe plans for a New Year\u2019s eve dance,\nbut decided to sponsor a dancing par\nty instead on Wednesday, Jan. 7,'in\nSt. Hedwige\u2019s hall\nMiss Ilildegarde Kruszewski, 1611\nW. Longley avenue, entertained mem\nbers of the W. W. W. club Tuesday\nnight at her home. The next meet\ning will be held on Dec. 30, at the\nhome of Miss Theresa Jackowlak, 929\nW. Washington avenue.\nA bunco and card party will be\nsponsored Thursday. Jan. 15, in St,\nHedwige\u2019s hall by the Children or\nMary society.\nSENTENCE KIDNAPERS\nTO LIFE IN PRISON\nBy lulled Pres*:.\nCOLUMBUS, Ind., Dec. 17.\u2014Pleas\nof insanity and drunkenness failed\nto save Arthur Cox, 28, from a sen\ntence to life impisonment on a charge\nof kidnaping Gloria Jean Huffer, 7,\nhere a few weeks ago.\nCox picked the girl up while she\nwas playing with a group of children.\nScreams of the children brought\nimmediate pursuit, and Cox was soon\ncaptured.\nThe kidnaper\u2019s wife testified that\nCox became morose when they dis\ncussed their four years of childless\nmarriage.\na\nft*\nil:\nI-:\ni1-,\nfv\n\nif\nfev\nft.\n1\ni\nK-r\ni;\nr\nC;\n-AT THE HOME FURNITURE COMPANY\nOur displays aie filled with toys that will last through\nthe year. Only the better kind are shown and they\nare priced exceptionally low. Pay after Christinas.\nTable and Chairs\nBassinette\nA doll bassinette, complete\nwith wheels J J\nam