u2014\"Amos \u2019n\u2019 Andy,\" the radio headliners, in a\nhumorous picture.\nRIVER PARK\u2014\"Children of Pleasure.\u201d\nCASTLE\u2014\u201cThe Little. Accident\u201d which puts Douglas Fair\nbanks, jr., in an embarrassing position and the\naudience in convulsions.\nOLIVER-\u2014Clara Bow in \u201cLove Among the Millionaires.\u201d\nMiss Hatpin reviews South Bend pictures and vaudeville\nin The News-Times the day following the opening.\nScene from \u201cThe Gorilla\u201d starring Joe Frisco and Lila Lee on the Palace\nscreen starting Wednesday.\nFIND CHICAGO GIRL\nASLEEP NEAR HOME\nBy International News Service:\nCHICAGO, Dec. 17.\u2014Margaret\nRuth Miller, 10, early today was\nfound asleep ana unharmed in the\nhallway of a building near her home.\nPolice had searched for her since\nTuesday afternoon, when she went to\na neighborhood store with $20 to do\nsome shopping for her mother.\nSCREEN STAR LEAVES\nESTATE OF $73,835\nBy International News Service:\nHOLLYWOOD, Calif., Dec, 17.\u2014\nMabel Normand, famous screen come\ndienne wdio died Feb. 23, left an es\ntate of $73,835 including a home\nworth $20,000 to her mother, Mrs.\nMary Normand of Staten Island, N.\nY.. according to an appraisal of her\nestate on file here today.\nBANK CLOSES DOORS\nTO AID DEPOSITORS\nBy l nlted Presn;\nRENSSELAER., Ind., Dec. 17.\u2014The\nTrust and Savings bank of Rensse\nlaer has been closed by directors to\nprotect the interests of depositors.\nCapitalization of the bank was\n$100,000, deposits $830,000, loans $770,\nC00, and undivided profits $10,000.\nE. J. Randle is president and Jud\nson J. Hunt, secretary and, treasurer.\nBLAME COMMUNISTS\nFOR LYONS BOMBING\nBy ITnlted Press:\nLYONS, France. Dec. 17.\u2014A bomb\nexploded at the Place De La Repub\nlique today, blowing out shop win\ndows and causing damage estimated\nat 100,000 francs.\nPolice said they suspected Com\nmunists.\nEXPERT\nPICTURE FRAMING\nReasonable Price.\nsmithalsop\n\u00ae*lo**Be\u201edP.W Company\nFeeto