 mystery\ndrama that has all\nAmerica in hysteri\ncal laughter!\nGORILLA\nwith\nJOE FRISCO LILA LEE\nEDDIE GRIBBON\nOn the program with\nRKO VAUDEVILLE\nThe Only Stage Show\nin Northern Indiana\nBOB RIPA\nPhenomenal Boy Juggler\nWALTER PAUL BRIANT\nThe Dream of a Moving Man\nFRIVOLITIES OF 1930\nA Diversion of Song and Dance\nBOUDOIR\nDIPLOMAT\nWith a royal command\nto love, he won victories\nfor his country in the\nBoudoirs of the enemy!\nBETTY COMPSON\nIAN KEITH\nJEANETTE LOFF\nSTARTING SATURDAY\nOTIS f/i/ickiCT**\nSKINNER MOIVICI\nA\ni\nOIL COMPANY HEADS j\nSEE BUSINESS BOOm|\nBy United Press: i\nINDIANAPOLIS, Dec. 17.\u2014A bet-\nter business outlook for 1931 is de-!\npic ted on the basis of \u201ccold figures,\u201d j\nthan most people realize, officials of j\nthe Standard Oil company (Indiana)\ntold representatives at the annual\nsales meeting of the central and\neastern districts, at their session\nhere.\nACCIDENT IS FATAL\nTO CAR CONDUCTOR\nBy United Preii*: I\nMARION, Ind.. Dec. 17.-John Gar\nvey, 64, died in Grant county hospital\nof Injuries suffered Sunday when he\nstepped into the path of an aute.\nGarvey was an interurban car con\nductor, and bad stepped to the side\nof the car when the auto struck him.\nLast Times Today\n^HO! SHO!\nTHEY\u2019RE HERE!\nFamous stars of the\nair Now on the\nscreen\u2014\nAMOS\n\"ANDY\nThe c h a racters\nwho have made\ntwenty million\nradios throb with\nlife in their first\ntalking picture.\nwith\nSue\nCarol\nIrene\nRich\nDuke\nEllington\nand His\nBand\nin\nCHj\u00a3CK \u00ab>d\nDOUBLE CHECK\n_ Also\n\u201cFIDDLESTICKS\"\nA Comedy\n\"THE PIRATES\"\nBeauty and Color\nMain or\nFloor bwC\nBalcony.. 15c\nChildren, ,10c\nSTRAND\nOLIVER i\nAmiHallj Perfect T\u00ablMt\u00bb_\nLast t! mbs today\nCLARA BOW in\n\u201cLOVE AMONG THE\nMILLIONAIRES\u201d\nIt\u2019* Gmt Fietore!\nTon'll Tike IIrr In Thi* One!\nComing\u2014Friday and Saturday, Dm.\n1* and S\u00bb\u2014\"SHOW BOAT,\u201d Zlegfleld\u2019*\n_ Big Sprrlai:\n1A NEW PRICES n